  "body": "### Description\r\n1. Enable `Wallet` and needed stuff to start a send transaction.\r\n2. Go to `My Accounts` tab and select one. (Then it appears the footer).\r\n3. Try to scroll down to see `Networks` and `Priority` options.\r\n\r\n**Expected:**\r\nUser can scroll down to see all popup options\r\n\r\n**Actual:**\r\nUser cannot scroll down if the list of `My Accounts` is big enough that it is not possible to detect the mouse area outside the list itself so it is not possible to scroll down.\r\n\r\n**COMMENT:** Footer hides the available area outsite the list that the mouse can get to scroll down. Maybe it needs some margins area also in the left and right sides to allow the user scroll into the whole popup and not only inside the list.\r\n\r\nSee video for better understanding (last scene trying to scroll down but cannot):\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/97019400/174982423-0d908a36-7175-4fec-8ab2-ec10dcb7028e.mov\r\n\r\n",
